{"/service/ndnp/arhi/batch_arhi_kangaskhan_ver02/data/sn89051338/00414213133/1920071601/0703.xml":{"full_text":"Which Way are Trade Winds Really Blowing I\n9\n(Everit B. Terhune, Gen. Mgr. Boot and Shoe Recorder.)\nIt is high time that a certain type of American business men cease worry\ning, and take comfort from some plain, easily-discoverable facts. I am getting a\ngrowing conviction that in some commercial quarters pessimism is masquerading\nas marvelous schrewdness, far-sightedness, conservatism.\nI sense the tendency on the part of a few business men here and there\nto construe present unusual commercial conditions as the inevitable forerunner of\npanic conditions.\nAlso, I ean put my finger on what I consider a very stupid inclination\namong certain thoughtless persons to shrug their shoulders at any mild suggestion\nthat the business of this country is not necessarily going to blow up with a loud\nand resonant crash within the next eighteen months!\nIf one has the interest to chase this pessimism to its source, then puts the\nsource under the magnifying glass of intelligent, unflamed business analysis of\nwhat does he find it to consist?\nJust this: Commodities are very high; the consuming public is crying more\nnearly in unison every day for lower prices; labor is in an aggrevated state of\nunrest; and commercial, social and political conditions in Europe are generally bad.\nGranted\u2014every bit of it!\nBut, even so, please permit some of us to retain our mental equilibrium;\nbear with us while we decline to become frenzied over these things and allow us\nfor a moment to put the facts through a laboratory test.\nWhich way are the \u201ctrade winds\u201d REALLY blowing?\nSo far as I know, or can find out, no business depression in the United\nStates ever occurred in or immediately following a period in which money was\nanywhere nearly as plentiful as it is today and has been for two years\u2014with a\nrecord-breaking gold balance to justify and even NECESSITATE it.\nSo far as I know or can find out, no commercial cataclysm in this country\nof ours has even come at a time of conspicuous under-production of necessities.\nOver-production has been a contributing cause of business lethargy.\nAnd so far as I know or can find out, no real business paralysis has ever\naccompanied or immediately succeeded a time when the working man\u2014or the\nfarmer\u2014was anywhere nearly so much master of his financial destiny as he ad\nmittedly is today, and is admittedly going to. continue to be for many years to\ncome.\nTruly,. I think the well-known volatile temper of the American business\nman has never been more strikingly demonstrated than in this silly inclination on\nthe part of a few of him to mistake the probably approaching readjustment of\ncommercial matters for a stagnation.\nAnd here, I think, we get the real answer: We shall have a CLARIFYING\nof industrial relations, a STRAIGHTENING-OUT of commodity values, and per\nhaps of trading prices and profit ratios\u2014but a panic, a business depression, a\nperiod of radical commercial curtailment, NO!\nI am quite satisfied to let the coming twenty-four months prove me a\nfalse or true prophet.\nWhat I am principally quarreling with is the superficial character of the\njudgment that a few self-appointed calamity-howlers always insist on applying\nto a business situation whenever it is anything but 100 per cent. rosy.\nThey can deal in nothing but extremes.\nThey like to interpret a prospective, natural easing-off of abnormally high\nprices as a bottom-dropped-out affair.\nThey view an upset labor situation as forecasting an industrial tragedy\u2014\nentirely forgetting, apparently, that a labor crisis never comes when production of\nliving necessities are tremendously under normal requirements.\nTo them the unparalleled accumulation of gold reserves in this country at\npresent, with its unavoidable influence toward high prices, high wages and popular\nextravagance, means nothing at all!\nTwo years ago everyone was proclaiming, truthfully, that \u201cbusiness in the\nUnited States is just entering an era of the greatest prosperity ever known.\u201d\nRIGHT!!\u2014and we ARE in it, and, if we will merely ignore or suppress the\nstupid croakers, we shall easily continue in that prosperity for many, many years.\nThe War set the international stage for this precise prosperity. By it we\nbecame, involuntarily, uncontrollably, the logical supply source for a good share\nof the rest of* the world for the major part of TEN YEARS\u2014probably longer.\nDo we business men of the United States now purpose throwing this ad\nvantage\u2014this responsibility\u2014to the four winds, merely to give foolish substance\nto the frothiness of a few false prophets whose teeth begin to chatter the moment\nthe consuming public pauses and reflectively scratches its chin?\nI talk business with a great many men influential in the shoe industry and\nin other lines; and believe me, I get FACTS.\nWe discuss production, sales promotion, distribution\u2014and advertising. A\nbusiness pape.r like The Boot and Shoe Recorder must get close to the REAL\nstructure of the country\u2019s commerce.\nIf I should epitomize the worth-while statements made to me of late by\nthe worth-while men of business, they would come down to about this:\n\u201cLet\u2019s not even dream of poor business while all about us\nwe have, and must for a long time have, the elements that always\nmake business SECURE.\u201d\n\u201cAny business man who thinks he can for see commercial de\npression when his own country and half the rest of the world are\nclamoring for goods ought to be surveyed by an alienist!\u201d\n\u201cWe should at least scratch the surface of our tremendous trade\nadvantage before we begin to wonder if we have exhausted it.\u201d\nI want to say that business journalism is an excellent barometer of com\ning business conditions. Advertisers are as canny as they make them! An ad\nvertiser can scent a distant slump in business more keenly than any other kind\nof business individauls I know.\nAdvertisers in the footwear field are not apprehensive of the future. Those\nwho are the real thinkers can see business in the United States on nothing but\na solid foundation\u2014made so by practically every economic factor required for\ncommercial security.\nYes, prices are going to be revised downward, some time; broadcast per\nsonal extravagance is going to run its course, and prosperous sanity return; labor\nis going to rub its eyes clear and jump enthusiastically into the pleasant and\nprofitable work of making production more nearly match the demand for it.\nWe are going to straighten out the situation, and bring America\u2019s business\nto its proper basis WITHOUT interrupting it?\nThe AMERICAN PEOPLE THEMSELVES\u2014of course!\nThey have always been able to get about anything on earth that they want\ned. They are ALWAYS the final controlling factor in our business life, if they\nwish to be.\nThey don\u2019t want business depression.\nTherefore, we are not going to have it.\nThe above article shows such splendid vision, such optimistic thoughl and\nbelief in the present and future welfare of the country that we are printing the\nsame as a part of our regular weekly advertisement. We hope we may be par\ndoned if in thus using our space, any person looking for the usual description\nof merchandise, shall be disappointed. Another time we will tell you about the\nlarge and constantly changing stock carried in this store, how it is possible to\nfind everything usually carried and many things not usually carried in such a\ntown as ours, but for the present we think it more important to give this \u201copin\nion upon the trend of business conditions in America.\u201d We have read the ar\nticle with great interest and we believe the same is expressive of the genuine\noptimism of the intelligently conservative people and we commend the point of\nview to everyone who is interested in seeing a safe and sane prosperity continue.\nThose who \u201cview with alarm\u201d every time the financial wind changes, who see\ntrouble always just ahead, don\u2019t get out of life what they should. Their worries are\nlargely imaginary, for the things that they look for seldom happen.\nWe think the fall business will be fine and we are making preparations\nto handle our share of wagons, buggies, implements, seeds, harness, hardware, dry\ngoods, groceries, feed, shoes and clothing.\n\n_ --\u2014ft -m\nWagons and Farm 11\nMachinery |1\n\n0-0\u20140\u20140\u20140\u20140\u20140\u20140\u2014o\u2014c\n0 CHURCHES o\n1 I\no\u2014o-o-o--o-o-o-o\nST. ANDREW\u2019S CHURCH\nThe Rev. C. C. Burke, Rector\nSUNDAYS\nHoly Communion_7:00 a. m.\nChurch School_9:30 a. m.\nMorning Prayer_11:00a. m.\nVespers _ 7:30 p. m.\nWEEK DAYS\nWednesdays Litany_10:00 a. m.\nThursdays, Holy Com\nmunion-7:00 a. m.\nFridays, Litany-7:30 p. m.\nHOLY DAYS\nHoly Communion_7:00 a. m.\nSt. Andrew\u2019s Guild meets Mon\ndays, 3 p. m.\nSt. Andrew\u2019s Parish Helpers\n|j\u00aeJ^fednesdays^J^3^jx^n^^^^\nTHE CHRISTIAN CHURCH\nBible school begins promptly at\n9:45. We have been having fine\nattendance at the Bible School dur\ning the hot weather but we do not\nto encourage old \u201cMr. Summer\nSlump,\u201d so we must work for a larg\ner attendance this Sunday than we\nhad last. Come out and enjoy the\nBible School hour with us.\nAt 11:00 a. m. preaching and\ncommunion service. The subject of\nthis hour will be \u201cThe Lord\u2019s Day.\u201d\nJunior Endeavor at four o\u2019clock.\nSenior Endeavor at seven o\u2019clock.\nTreadling service at quarter to\neight. The subject of the evening\nwill be the \u201cDawn of a New Day.\u201d\nWe invite you to come out and wor\nship with us.\nR. V. SAYLOR,\nPastor.\nFIRST PRESBYTERIAN CHURCH\nAttendance at the regular Com\nmunion service last Sunday was\nquite an improvement over the last\ncommunion service in March. I\nhope the time is before u. when no\nmember shall miss this service.\nPastor preached up to Wednesday\nnight of this week at Oak Forest.\nIf the roads get passable the meet?\ning will continue and close out there\nSaturday night. In the afternoon\nat three o\u2019clock, pastor will preach\nat Brickey. Good attendance want\ned. The meeting announced out\nthere will be put off until the early\npart of September on account of\ncrop work, etc. So many away\nAugust. Preaching service 11 a. ir\nNo service in town Sunday night. I\nWe shall be glad to have a full at-1\ntendance at the 11 a. m. service.\n\nr\nSuccessful Men\nKNOW THE VALUE\nOF A BANK\nA bank aided them to achieve their success.\nh _\nIt saved their money when they had little, and\npaid them interest on those savings.\nIt loaned them money to branch out in business,\nand counseled and advised with them in order to\nmake that branching a success from the start.\n\nThe modern road to success begins at the saving w\\p\ndow of a bank. Are you acquainted with such a\nwindow?\nBank of Commerce\n\nMusic by the choir and congrega\ntion. Subject 11 a. m. \u201cChristian\nGrowth.\u201d Christians are not per\nfected here. But growing toward\nthe matured life in Christ. Be at\nSunday school and our morning\nservice.\nW. K. JOHNSTON,\n-o\nCOTTON SQUARE BORER\nMAKES ITS APPEARANCE\nSmall green catapillars which have\nbeen observed damaging the cotton\ncrop near Van Buren known as the\ncotton square borer, according to\na statement from W. J. Baerg, en\ntomologist of the College of Agri\nculture, University of Arkansas.\nThe caterpillar is a velvety green,\nfrom one half to three quarters of\nan inch in length, and oval in out\nline, states Mr. Baerg. The pest\nprefers to attack the cotton squares\nthat are developing, hollow them\nout and often boring into the ten\nder stalks.\nFor the past week or so the cat\nerpillars have been in the pupal or\nresting stage and the moths are due\nto appear within a few days. The\ncaterpillars are the larvae of a\ndainty butterfly, bluish black in\ncolor, with a reddish lustre. The\nfemale butterflies lay the eggs, yel\nlow in color, on the underside of\nthe leaves of the cotton, bean and\ncow-pea plants. It is believed that\nbeans and peas are preferred to\nam TUa a\u00bb/vo Viof/>K in f rn m\ntwo to five days. The next gener\nation is likely to appear within a\nweek from now. Probably three\ngenerations appear within the year.\nIt is claimed that, as a rule, the\nJune generation of the cotton square\nborer is very heavily parasitized.\nParasites of various kinds attack\nthe caterpillers in such large num\nbers that very few of them live to\ntransform into adult butterflies. It\nis somewhat hazardous to make a\nprediction in regard to the number\nof caterpillars that will appear in\nthe next generation, but it seems\nnow that they will not cause any\nvery serious injury. However it\nwill be well to observe the cotton\ncarefully during the next week for\nthe appearance of the borers.\nIn case the caterpillars should\nturn up in considerable numbers the\ncotton should be dusted with cal\ncium arsenate in the same manner\nas is done for the control of the\ncotton boll weevil. If the dusters\north e calcium arsenate cannot be\nsecured, lead arsenate may be used\nand applied as a spray. Several\nfarmers near Van Buren have de\nvised small spraying outfit that are\napparently doing fairly good work.\nDusting machinery and calcium\narsenate can be bought from the\nNiagare Sprayer Company, Vicks\nburg, Mississippi and the Grasselli\nChemical Company, New Orleans.\n-o\nColumbia University should give\nNicholas Murray Butler more to\ndo.\u2014Boston Transcript.\nIn Russia the brotherhood of man\nseems to be working out in about\nthe same way it does in every fam\nily where there are four boys who\nall want the flivver Sunday night.\n\u2014Philadelphia Inquirer.\n-o\nSenator Johnson on his long,\nweary ride home from Chicago,\ndoubtless recalled the persistent in\ndividual of whom it was said he\ntook nothing from the pie-counter\nbut his elbows.\u2014New Haven Journ\nal-Courier.\n-:0\nLook not upon the whine when it\nis red. -Newark (Ohio) Star-Aagle.\nSA/VS/WWVWWVWWVWWWWWSACVW^\nI J. A. HORNE\nNOTARY PUBLIC\nOFFICE\nLEE COUNTY LAND, LOAN\nAND ABSTRACT CO.\nSecond Floor, Letter Building\nHave you tried\na bottle of the\nNew Cook's\nGold b lume?\nIt\u2019s the /teat thing\nYou'll 90/ 90\n-0\n\u201cAH profiteers will go straight to\nhell!\u2019\u2019 shouts a Baltimore minister.\nLook out, then, for a raise in the\nprice of matches.\u2014Louisville Times.\n-o\nGermany is buying hemp in large\nquantities. If we w:ere the ex\nKaiser we wouldn\u2019t go back home\njust now.\u2014Charleston News and\nCourier.\n-o\nIt has been judicially declared\nthat woolen cloth is not clothing,\nwhich is as simple as the fact that\nvery little clothing is woolen cloth.\n\u2014Philadelphia Press.\n-o\nAccording to recent figures from\nBradstreet\u2019s, 84 per cent of all\nbusiness failures are among non\nadvertisers.\nO. C. Sutton Co. I\nManufacturers of and Dealers in\nBrick, Lime and Cement I\nSend or Write o Us and Get Prices. We Can I\nSave You Money. TELEPHONE 165\nMARIANNA ICE STORAGE CO.\nPhone 218\nManufacturers of\nPure Distilled Water Ice and\nCarbonated Drinks\nOpen for business: Week days, 6 a. m. to 7 p. m.\nSundays, 8 a. m. to noon. No ice sold before or after\nhours.","height":"29720","width":"19552"}}
